INSERT INTO `question` (`id`, `quiz_id`, `title`, `type`, `number_of_options`, `options`, `correct_answers`, `order`) VALUES ('1', '1', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: inter-regular, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;1) Which of the following is the correct name of React.js?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"a. React\",\"b. React.js\",\"c. ReactJS\",\"d. All of the above\"]', '[\"2\"]', '1'), ('2', '1', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: inter-regular, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;2) Which of the following are the advantages of React.js?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '4', '[\"a. React.js can increase the application\'s performance with Virtual DOM.\",\"b. React.js is easy to integrate with other frameworks such as Angular, BackboneJS since it is only a view library.\",\"c. React.js can render both on client and server side.\",\"d. All of the above\"]', '[\"4\"]', '2'), ('3', '1', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: inter-regular, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;3) Which of the following is not a disadvantage of React.js?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '4', '[\"a. React.js has only a view layer. We have put your code for Ajax requests, events and so on.\",\"b. The library of React.js is pretty large.\",\"c. The JSX in React.js makes code easy to read and write.\",\"d. The learning curve can be steep in React.js.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '3'), ('4', '1', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: inter-regular, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;4) Which of the following command is used to install create-react-app?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '4', '[\"a. npm install -g create-react-app\",\"b. npm install create-react-app\",\"c. npm install -f create-react-app\",\"d. install -g create-react-app\"]', '[\"1\"]', '4'), ('5', '1', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: inter-regular, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;5) What of the following is used in React.js to increase performance?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '4', '[\"a. Original DOM\",\"b. Virtual DOM\",\"c. Both A and B.\",\"d. None of the above.\"]', '[\"2\"]', '5'), ('6', '5', '&lt;h2 style=&quot;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 20px; font-size: 1.25em !important;&quot;&gt;1. Who develop react.js?&lt;/h2&gt;', 'single_choice', '2', '[\"Apple\",\"Facebook\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('7', '5', '&lt;h2 style=&quot;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 20px; font-size: 1.25em !important;&quot;&gt;2. What are props into other components&lt;/h2&gt;', 'single_choice', '2', '[\"properties\",\"state\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('8', '9', '&lt;h1 style=&quot;font-size: 2em; margin-top: 0.67em; margin-bottom: 0.67em; line-height: 45px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &amp;quot;Apple Color Emoji&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Emoji&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Symbol&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;1. What is the purpose of the &quot;key&quot; prop in React?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h1&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"a) It uniquely identifies a component in an array of components. \",\"b) It determines the visual styling of a component. \",\"c) It specifies the route for navigation within a React application. \",\"d) It defines the data type of a component\'s prop. \"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('9', '9', '&lt;h1 style=&quot;font-size: 2em; margin-top: 0.67em; margin-bottom: 0.67em; line-height: 45px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &amp;quot;Apple Color Emoji&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Emoji&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Symbol&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;2. What is the state of React class component?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h1&gt;', 'single_choice', '4', '[\"a) A JavaScript method for sorting arrays. \",\"b) A built-in object that stores component data. \",\"c) A CSS class used for component styling. \",\"d) A React component\'s initial render method. \"]', '[\"1\"]', '0');
